What is BRAF? Yes, they were zero-length, at least according to ls and eclipse' debugger and I even deleted the files and recreated equally named, empty files manually :) 

IMHO code like

  int foo = 0;

  while(whatever) { whatever }

  bar / foo;

is always broken. A simple additional if-throw-IOException won't hurt and will help to grasp things faster.
